          "annotations": [
            {
              "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f66/canvas/p3/annopage",
              "type": "AnnotationPage",
              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f66/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(1)\">From having been assailed in the pages of the\n                                        Occident. I desire<lb/> that the same channel should be used\n                                        to remove the <del>expression</del> aspersion,<lb/>\n                                        therefore, I furnish you, as its Editor, with the above\n                                        Extract from my letter<lb/> book requesting that you will in\n                                        the next number, give place in your<lb/> own name, to a\n                                        lucid and satisfactory explanation, for you must<lb/>\n                                        readily perceive, and acknowledge, how indiscreet was the\n                                        statement,<lb/> and arrogant the assumption expressed by\n                                        you, when you stated<lb/> “that the publication of the\n                                                  <add>?</add> of the Editor of the Asmonean\n                                        would<lb/> injure him, and increase your circulation.”</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I shall not deign to comment on the evident bad\n                                        taste which<lb/> induced you, a professor of Divinity, to\n                                        pen the following “a charge which<lb/> we do not care <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">just now</hi> to bring down upon\n                                        us” the words undeserved<lb/> by me, may possibly have\n                                        reference to your present hostile position<lb/> with your\n                                        congregation, or may prospectively regard the forthcoming\n                                        “Jewish<lb/> Advocate” but ere the Editor of the Occident\n                                        wrote <hi rend=\"underline\">just now</hi> he<lb/> should have\n                                        recollected, that I, as the Editor of the Asmonean, did<lb/>\n                                        through its agent at <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n                                        <persName>Mr Michael Allen</persName>, place its\n                                        columns<lb/> at the service of the <persName>Rev Isaac\n                                                  Leeser</persName> to answer and refute the\n                                        charges<lb/> of his opponents. And further that I am in\n                                        possession of two notes<lb/> wherein <persName>Mr\n                                                  Leeser</persName> writes “that he is greatly\n                                        obliged to the Editor<lb/> of the Asmonean for his dignified\n                                        notice of A Review; and in the<lb/> second <persName>Mr\n                                                  Leeser</persName> requests a notice, and remarks\n                                        “that he is not<lb/> ungrateful for favors conferred”</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">It matters little to me, how you act with respect\n                                        to notices or<lb/> reports; the Asmonean while under my\n                                        charge will be conducted as<lb/> I deem fit, but if you\n                                        refer to an editorial of mine published</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f66/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
