                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f66/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p><date>July the fifth</date> you will perceive that I publicly\n                                        announced that matters<lb/> of public import or general\n                                        interest would be inserted gratis, but that<lb/> matter for\n                                        private ends would be subject to charge. However if I\n                                        do<lb/> see fit sometimes to depart form this rule of the\n                                        profession, the <placeName>Albany</placeName><lb/> affair\n                                        was not one to induce me. But this week I shall do so,\n                                        and<lb/> shall publish gratuitously a series of resolutions\n                                        laudatory of yourself<lb/> and concerning the Occident. And\n                                        I do this with the feelings<lb/> that invariably actuate\n                                        me—to wit—a perfect contempt for personal<lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add>, and a desire to forward everything having a\n                                        tendency<lb/> to elevate the intellect and humanise the\n                                        affections of my<lb/> fellow men.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">As I am particularly desirous that this matter\n                                        should<lb/> be entirely cleared up before your next issue of\n                                        the Occident<lb/> I must press upon you for an early reply\n                                        stating the course<lb/> you purport taking</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">I am Dear Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\">yours Respectfully</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(10)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Rob Lyon</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <div>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_8_5.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text refers to Occident Volume 8 No. 5 pages 255\n                                                  through 257. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_8_6.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text refers to Occident Volume 8 No. 6 pages 306\n                                                  through 312. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                              </div>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f66/canvas/p4"
                }
              ]
